{
    "name": "Nymph",
    "type": "monster_family",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Nymph Queens",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Artistic Treasures",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Nymphs favor art over any other types of material possession, often collecting the finest pieces they can and endeavoring to create their own. Nymphs sometimes carry magical trinkets or wear enchanted clothing or jewelry, but the greatest treasure a nymph queen can share is often her inspiration to those seeking a muse.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 244,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Dual Guardians",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "While all nymphs protect areas of natural beauty, hesperides often guard other unusual treasures of a more literal variety, sometimes including items long thought lost. Their steady temperaments and timeless loyalty ensure that they can be trusted to keep whatever they\u2019re protecting safe from harm.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 244,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Harmonious Landscapes",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Nymphs tend to be closely associated with specific areas of natural splendor and beauty\u2014woodlands for dryads, rivers for naiads. Areas where nymphs dwell always look more pristine, breathtaking, and scenic than they would otherwise.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 244,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Inspirations for Art",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Nymphs are living manifestations of beauty and grace, and as such they are often the subjects of art\u2014sculpture and paintings in particular. Promising a nymph to immortalize them in a work of art can be an excellent way to secure that nymph's favor, but one should take care to ensure that the nymph admires and is proud of the artistic effort's final result, lest the nymph be insulted and lash out with her powerful magic.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 244,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "name": "Other Nymphs",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Naiads and dryads are the most well-known nymphs, but others exist as well. Hesperides, for example, are warders of the sunset and golden light and can be encountered dwelling on coastal cliffsides or remote islands. Lampads, on the other hand, are dark, moody nymphs found in wondrous, crystal-lined caverns deep underground.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            },
                            "page": 244,
                            "errata": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "1.1",
                                "alt": "1.1",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 221
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "text": "Nymph queens are powerful nymphs who rule over entire regions of untouched wilderness, not just single trees or ponds. Every variety of nymph can have a queen. Naiad queens are among the most prominent, and more often interact with nearby mortals. Thus, some scholars refer to naiad queens as simply \u201cnymphs.\u201d",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                        "alt": "Monster Core pg. 244",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 221
                    },
                    "page": 244,
                    "errata": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "1.1",
                        "alt": "1.1",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 221
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
